<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="148" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="19.[173,1382,1044,2221]" pageId="19" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,527,1832,1865]" pageId="19" pageNumber="148">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. Reig’s Opossum is known only from two localities. One of these is found in Canaima National Park, Venezuela (type locality), but itis argued that Reig’s Opossum is under some risk due to human activities in and around the park, such as fires and selective logging. Within its Venezuelan distribution, a major international road, high-voltage power lines, and tourist activity represent potential disturbances in Canaima National Park, all the way to the border with Brazil. Gold and diamond mining also occur in the area, although only at lower elevations near the park’s boundary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
